<TEXT>
a somber tolling of the campus carillon at 
iowa state university on monday marked the five years isu graduate 
terry anderson has been held hostage in lebanon 
yellow ribbons were tied around trees outside the schools 
memorial union and posters with andersons picture proclaimed we 
have not forgotten 
but most students just back from spring break went about their 
business on campus without stopping for the noon ceremony some 
noticing television news crews asked reporters whats going 
on 
anderson a 1974 journalism and political science graduate of 
isu and a former des moines broadcaster is chief middle east 
correspondent for the associated press anderson was taken hostage 
in beirut on march 16 1985 and is the longest held western 
hostage in lebanon 
the isu ceremony marking the fifth anniversary of his capture 
was delayed from friday to monday to wait for students to return to 
the central iowa campus from spring break 
the carillon tolled 60 times about once each 10 seconds to 
mark the months anderson has spent in captivity 
