<TEXT>
when igor lukashuk opens an american law book he 
sees the future of the soviet union 
lukashuk a prominent international law expert hopes his 
research on american constitutional law carefully recorded in a 
big black notebook will act as a catalyst in shaping his countrys 
new political system 
the future communist party will be like your system the 
63yearold muscovite said it would suit us perfectly a two 
party system two parties that are different but really the same 
lukashuk is teaching soviet law at emory university in a newly 
established visiting professorship believed to be the first time a 
soviet academic institution is staffing an american university on a 
continual basis 
it took two years of negotiations and a letter from former 
president jimmy carter urging soviet leader mikhail gorbachev to 
endorse the program but the professorship was established last 
fall with the institute of state and law of the ussr academy of 
sciences 
lukashuk a frequent united nations delegate welcomed the 
chance to study how typical americans are treated by their 
political system 
but he spends most of his time answering questions from crowds 
of students and journalists who flock to his office rather than 
asking them an enthusiastic i explain you why punctuates his 
conversations 
all the time people ask me about gorbachev if im a 
communist said the longtime communist party member 
i believe in gorbachev hes a gifted man he added but 
according to marxism socialism develops due to contradictions but 
there are no contradictions with only one party 
lukashuk is asked frequently how he likes the united states he 
is careful not to criticize but will say he thinks americans are a 
little too arrogant 
i cant agree with your president that the world needs the 
leadership of the us he explained tomorrow will be a 
welfare world its not possible to make a secure world if the us 
is inventing butter without fat while other people are starving 
lukashuk is also critical of the soviet political system hes 
trying to change saying it destroyed his countrys economy and 
contributed to ethnic violence in armenia and azerbaijan and calls 
for independence by the baltic republics 
for five years we supported perestroika but still we must 
eat he said they must make the first steps so that in 
february it is just a bit better than january 
making gorbachevs policy of perestroika or restructuring work 
lies in finding out what makes systems such as those of the united 
states and great britain work lukashuk said thats his goal 
and even though he says he can do more research in atlanta in 
three months than in moscow in a year hes having a hard time 
fitting work into his schedule people keep calling asking for 
interviews or inviting him to parties lukashuk said he just cant 
turn anyone down especially not students 
they are understandable in law understandable in life of 
humor jokes lukashuk said i must say they are more sincere 
more open than students in other countries they are the future of 
the world community 
</TEXT>
