<TEXT>
an agreement to end a fiveday 
antiabortion filibuster in the state senate apparently unraveled 
monday as both sides held firm in the debate over an 
abortionrights bill 
the agreement had been announced late sunday by senate president 
thomas v mike miller the democrat had said it was acceptable to 
32 senators enough to pass a motion of cloture that would end the 
filibuster which began thursday 
both sides however said the agreement was based on a 
misunderstanding over a compromise proposed by an antiabortion 
legislator the misunderstanding became apparent only when 
negotiators attempted to put the finishing touches to it 
negotiating teams meet several times monday morning but the 
talks were suspended in the afternoon when both sides refused to 
budge from their positions the antiabortion senators insisted 
they were prepared to carry on the debate indefinitely 
we proposed a very reasonable compromise said democratic 
