would effectively include two bills a prochoice measure that 
would go into effect immediately and a second more restrictive 
section favored by antiabortion senators 
underlying that proposal was the assumption that any bill 
approved and signed into law would immediately be challenged and 
wind up in a referendum 
under the proposal if the voters rejected the first section 
the second the restrictive one automatically would become law 
abortion rights legislators said monday they hadnt gone along 
with the twotier bill but that the other side had mistakenly 
thought they had they acknowledged however the suggestion was 
being considered in mondays talks 
