abortions would be regulated in each of the two sections 
the original bill was drafted in expectation that the us 
supreme court will overturn the 1973 roe vs wade decision 
legalizing abortions 
the bill would allow unrestricted abortions until a fetus is 
able to survive outside the womb after fetal viability is reached 
abortions would be allowed only to save a womans life or protect 
her health 
negotiators said the postviability question was another serious 
obstacle to an agreement 
abortion rights activists want a law that would allow such 
abortions to protect a womans mental health as well as to save 
her life or protect her physical health 
antiabortionists would like to restrict postviability 
abortions to those necessary to save the life of the mother or at 
the most to protect her physical health 
