armed services committee delegation to morocco egypt jordan 
oman bahrain and portugal in 11 days 
the delegation met a king a sultan and a president they ate 
pigeon saw the pyramids and cruised the nile but these pleasures 
were mingled with hours of embassy briefings meetings with foreign 
officials and banquets 
by the end of the trip members and staffers were saying it 
was like the bataan death march said rep patricia schroeder 
dcolo who organized the trip as chairman of the armed services 
subcommittee on military installations 
schroeder said 18hour days were the norm on her trip adding 
there were no golf clubs no tanning clinics the food was 
very good but i dont think we ever sat down to a dinner that was 
less than three hours long 
