<TEXT>
a teenager taking drugs is three times more 
likely to attempt suicide than nondrug users suggesting that 
marijuana alcohol and other drugs play a powerful role in suicide 
among the young according to a new study 
theres no question that the drugs themselves can lead to 
depressive effects that lead to suicide attempts said dr 
richard h schwartz a vienna va pediatrician who coauthored 
the study among the youth the more easily obtainable is the 
drug the greater the adverse effects suicide attempts increase 
dramatically 
the study by schwartz and by alan l berman a member of the 
psychology department faculty at american university is published 
this month in the american journal of diseases of children 
suicide is the third leading cause of death among americans aged 
15 to 24 and in virginia where schwartz practices suicide is the 
second leading cause of death among this age group 
schwartz said his study involved testing and questioning of 298 
adolescent patients in four treatment centers he identified as 
being in three separate areas east of the mississippi river 
twothirds of those surveyed admitted they had thoughts about 
committing suicide and 89 or 30 percent said they had made 
actual suicide attempts 
earlier studies said schwartz shows that only 6 percent to 7 
percent of the general adolescent population attempts suicide 
schwartz said the patients in his study were between 13 and 19 
years of age ninetythree percent were white and 66 percent were 
male 
the most popular drug among the group was marijuana with 
alcohol a distant second but other drugs such as crack cocaine 
angel dust and lsd also were used 
among those who attempted suicide 40 percent said they made the 
attempt within eight hours after using drugs 
schwartz said though there probably are multiple factors 
that lead to suicide attempts he believes the higher number of 
attempts among drug users may be attributed to the depressive 
effects of some drugs or to the low that develops after using 
drugs such as cocaine or crack 
some drugs in and of themselves have depressive effects 
alcohol does and so does pcp angel dust and lsd said 
schwartz for drugs that are stimulants such as crack or cocaine 
the depression is a rebound they go up very high and the higher 
the high the lower the low 
most of the suicide attempts were of low lethality said 
schwartz with 61 percent requiring no medical attention but 10 
percent tried to kill themselves at the wheel of a car and 8 
percent tried to hang themselves 
about 15 percent of those who attempted suicide spent time 
in intensive care said schwartz these were not superficial 
wrist slashings but serious attempts that could have resulted in 
death without prompt medical care 
schwartz said he and berman were astounded to learn that 23 
percent of those who tried to kill themselves said their families 
still kept firearms and ammunition around the home after the 
suicide attempt 
you cannot keep weapons at home like that if there is an 
adolescent on drugs you can assume a one in nine chance of 
multiple suicide attempts so you need to get rid of firearms 
said schwartz among successful suicides theres a growing 
tendency to use firearms 
</TEXT>
