<TEXT>
efforts to ban semiautomatic assault weapons 
speed up appeals in death penalty cases and permit searches without 
warrants are generating new heat in the senate as lawmakers brace 
for an electionyear anticrime debate 
we cannot win the drug fight without tough criminal laws 
sen orrin hatch rutah said of the legislation which the senate 
is expected to tackle soon now that members are returning from last 
weeks recess 
the bill began in the senate as an anticrime package 
recommended by president bush 
majority democrats however made major changes and the 
administration opposes the bill being brought to the floor by 
judiciary committee chairman joseph r biden jr ddel 
but republicans still hope it can be retailored to suit white 
house tastes 
divisions are so deep that few if any senators would be 
shocked to see the bill filibustered to death conservatives wince 
at the notion of adding more guncontrol legislation while senate 
liberals have little stomach for expanding use of the death penalty 
no matter how brutal the crime a person has committed the 
