society says sen edward m kennedy dmass the death penalty 
is a dead end in the war on crime 
both bidens bill and a gop rival sponsored by sen strom 
thurmond rsc would reinstate the death penalty for 30 federal 
crimes including assassination of the president such a law has 
been on the books for decades but supreme court decisions in the 
1970s blocked courts from imposing death in those cases 
both bills also would set deadlines for death row inmates to 
file federal appeals or forfeit their right to do so the idea is 
to prevent delays that sometimes drag out for a decade 
the result is a criminal justice system which is overburdened 
with piecemeal and repetitious litigation and years of delay 
between sentencing and a final judicial resolution of the criminal 
matter thurmond says 
but critics say defendants should have the maximum chance to 
avoid being sent to the execution chamber contending the death 
sentence is sometimes applied in a haphazard or discriminatory 
manner 
the democratic proposal would allow a second round of appeals 
for any prisoner victimized by a miscarriage of justice on his 
first try 
kennedy also wants to allow those awaiting execution to argue 
that capital punishment was imposed on them as part of a 
statistical pattern of bias against minorities 
but hatch contends the provision is transparently designed to 
abolish the death penalty in all cases and that would kill the 
crime bill without a doubt 
meanwhile republicans want to allow courts in some cases to 
admit evidence obtained in searches carried out without warrants if 
police acted in good faith 
the democratic bill primarily echoes the latest supreme court 
ruling on this exclusionary rule which allows courts in some 
circumstances to admit evidence obtained in a flawed manner but 
not without a warrant 
democrats also want to widen the opportunity for defendants to 
get evidence thrown out of court 
manufacture sale and possession of nine types of semiautomatic 
assault weapons would be banned under the biden bill the american 
