<TEXT>
portauprince haiti ap in a dramatic shift of power last 
week from the army to civilians this impoverished country moved 
closer to democracy than it has been since the fall of the 29year 
duvalier family dictatorship in 1986 
but ertha pascaltrouillot the new provisional president still 
faces the possibility of a backlash from diehards in the 
illdisciplined 6000man army this caribbean nations 
traditional power broker 
there still are duvalierist death squads who oppose change 
said victor benoit coleader of a political coalition that 
spearheaded the fall of the latest military regime theyre armed 
and we know theyre very mad about the shift in power 
mrs pascaltrouillot also inherits an economy destroyed by 
decades of plundering and political turmoil in a land with few 
natural resources and not enough food for its 51 million people 
but the flight of military ruler lt gen prosper avril last 
week in the face of a popular uprising and the unconditional 
submission of the army high command to a civilian caretaker 
government could become a watershed in haitian history 
barring another coup haiti could within three to six months 
have its first democratically elected government since gaining 
independence from france in 1804 after a slave revolt 
we hope this new caretaker government will finally create an 
atmosphere for holding free elections so the people can for once 
choose the leaders they want said louis roy main author of the 
1987 constitution 
the last attempt to hold free and fair elections in november 
1987 were thwarted after thugs protected by soldiers killed at 
least 34 voters 
university professor leslie manigat was elected as a civilian 
president the following january but the vote was widely regarded 
as fraudulent the army retained effective control and ousted 
manigat in june 1988 
mrs pascaltrouillot a 46yearold supreme court judge and 
haitis first woman president is to govern along with a 19member 
state council comprised exclusively of civilians that will have 
veto power over her decisions 
in handing over power at mrs pascaltrouillots inauguration 
tuesday maj gen herard abraham told her madame president of 
the republic the armed forces of haiti are yours to command 
it appeared the armys most complete submission to the civilian 
political opposition since the generals took control when 
jeanclaude baby doc duvalier fled into exile in france ending 
the tyranny begun by his father the late francois papa doc 
the ouster of duvalier was not the end of the dictatorship it 
