recovered it now for the time being 
avril former financial adviser to the duvaliers took over 18 
months ago in a coup led by rankandfile soldiers demanding 
democratic reforms and an end to statesponsored violence the coup 
ousted the tyrannical lt gen henri namphy who had led two 
governments since duvalier 
avril pledged to turn over power to a civilian government in 
democratic elections this year and won praise from the us 
government for his campaign against drugtrafficking 
but human rights violations continued and avril was beginning 
to look more and more like a dictator in january his government 
brutally cracked down on the opposition rounding up and beating 
scores of critics and expelling seven prominent political leaders 
in response haitis major political parties announced they 
would boycott any election held under avrils rule assuming he 
would rig the vote 
on march 5 a soldier shot and killed an 11yearold girl while 
she was studying on her porch in the rural town of petit goave 
although the shooting appeared accidental it unleashed five days 
of nationwide protests 
avril resigned on march 10 and fled into exile in the united 
states two days later on a us air force transport at least 25 
people were killed and scores injured mostly in clashes between 
protesters and the security forces 
the united states and france haitis two main donors helped 
bring about avrils ouster and have said financial aid will be 
restored under a democratic government us ambassador alvin adams 
said he visited avrils home on the eve of his departure to 
persuade him to leave the country because of continuing civil 
unrest 
the 12member unity assembly the civic and political coalition 
that led the protests against avril says the new governments 
first priorities will be to organize elections and to make that 
possible keep a firm grip on the army and disarm marauding gunmen 
</TEXT>
