<TEXT>
here is a chronology of some key events in 
german history starting with world war i 
june 1914 archduke ferdinand heir to the austrian throne is 
assassinated triggering world war i imperial germany and austria 
are initially pitted against france russia and britain 
june 1919 defeated germany signs the tough treaty of 
versailles which awards 13 percent of its prewar territory to 
neighbors sets wideranging reparations and dissolves the reichs 
prussianbased military command 
august 1919 the new german republics constitution is adopted 
by an assembly in weimar 
november 1923 adolf hitler whose extremeright national 
socialist workers party rails against the versailles treaty makes 
a first grab for national power with the abortive beerhall 
putsch in munich 
jan 30 1933 hitler is appointed reich chancellor amid 
political chaos and mass unemployment of the great depression the 
nazis using slogans mixing populism assertion of germanys 
identity and antisemitism had become the biggest party in the 
weimar republic parliament hitler ruthlessly consolidates 
dictatorial powers within months 
sept 1 1939 hitlers army invades poland setting off world 
war ii 
may 8 1945 the third reich accepts unconditional surrender 
after the allied victory in a war that devastated much of europe 
and killed 55 million people france britain the united states 
and soviet union divide germany and its capital berlin into 
occupation zones 
june 5 1945 the ussovietbritish potsdam agreement awards 
eastern german areas mostly to poland 
may 23 1949 west germany formally know as the federal 
republic is founded in the three western occupation zones bonn 
becomes the capital 
oct 7 1949 the german democratic republic east germany is 
founded in the soviet zone east berlin is proclaimed the capital 
june 17 1953 soviet troops help east germanys communist 
authorities put down a popular uprising 
may 5 1955 west germany enters nato and becomes sovereign 
aug 13 1961 east germany builds the berlin wall to seal the 
last western escape route for its citizens 35 million of whom had 
left the soviet zone or east germany since 1945 
march 19 1970 chancellor willy brandt architect of improved 
west german relations with the soviet bloc in the late 1960s meets 
with east german premier willi stoph 
sept 3 1971 in the fourpower agreement the soviets 
guarantee west berlins ties with west germany including traffic 
links and allow west berliners to visit the citys eastern half 
and east germany 
dec 21 1972 after long negotiations east germany and west 
germany sign a basic agreement aimed at expanding ties 
oct 1 1982 helmut kohl a conservative replaces social 
democrat helmut schmidt as west german chancellor 
oct 18 1989 following massive popular protests hardline 
communist leader erich honecker steps down in east germany after 18 
years in power 
nov 9 1989 honeckers shortlived successor egon krenz 
opens the berlin wall and the rest of east germanys western border 
sunday east germany holds is its first free parliamentary 
elections and a conservative coalition favoring rapid reunification 
wins nearly 50 percent of the vote 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

