sundays election they are the leading party in the threeparty 
alliance for germany which won 482 percent of the vote and 193 of 
the 400 parliamentary seats that was more than preelection polls 
predicted 
the vote marked the first time east germans were given a free 
choice at polls after a decade of the nazis and 41 years of 
communist dictatorship 
de maiziere reading a statement by the alliance said the group 
wanted to build a possible grand coalition 
therefore we are inviting the social democrats and the union 
