hometown listeners as well as the millions of visitors to the smoky 
mountains she said in a statement 
at age 9 ms parton went with her uncle bill owens to wsev to 
tape two songs they had written together puppy love and girl 
left alone it was their first single for gold band records 
the quality of the recording would be considered substandard 
compared to todays technology because it was recorded through a 
single microphone former wsev comanagers mary sue poe and skip 
trotter said in a statement 
the theme park plans to display the original microphone and 
other equipment ms parton used to tape the two songs visitors 
also will be able to see the modern station in operation 
