weekend and a sajudis spokesman andreas ajubalis said it declared 
that lithuanias parliament has the mandate to enter negotiations 
with the ussr government 
the main thing now is to reach an agreement in principle in 
starting the negotiating process he said 
bickauskas who is also a deputy in the national supreme soviet 
said at todays kremlin session that the situation in the republic 
was normal and the lithuanian government is in control 
he said the lithuanian legislature on saturday confirmed its 
decision to declare independence and urged the soviet union to 
solve the issue through interstate talks 
lithuania along with the other baltic republics of latvia and 
estonia was forcibly annexed by the soviet union in 1940 
gorbachev speaking to reporters after voting in local runoff 
elections in moscow on monday continued to insist the lithuanian 
break was illegal and must be decided by the entire soviet union 
he said economic political cultural and technical ties were 
too strong to tear apart and human contacts have become 
particularly deep so it is a futile attempt to destroy them he 
expressed concern for lithuanias ethnic minorities mainly 
russians and poles 
nikolai medvedev a member of the lithuanian delegation and a 
deputy in the national congress said in an interview at the 
congress today that they hoped to meet with gorbachev today but no 
appointment had been set 
we are here and waiting to be called he said we will 
stay here as long as it takes 
he said he did not expect an immediate start to negotiations 
there will be some delay as the issues are contemplated then 
negotiations will start at the official level and eventually 
actual negotiations 
on saturday landsbergis appealed to democratic nations for 
official recognition of his new government so far no country has 
recognized lithuanian independence 
