negotiating a trade agreement with the soviets wiping away nearly 
half a century of trade friction 
the package would include granting mostfavored nation trading 
status qualifying the soviet union for the lowest tariffs 
available to american trading partners soviet exports into the 
united states currently bear duties as much as 10 times higher than 
imports from other nations 
