the man who may decide who will head israels 
new government is an unlikely kingmaker a 69yearold rabbi better 
known for his torah scholarship than foreign policy 
rabbi ovadia yosef spiritual leader of the ultraorthodox shas 
party made his power felt earlier when he put aside his daily task 
of guiding his flock and advised prime minister yitzhak shamir to 
accept usbacked peace proposals 
shamir said no and yosef then used his spiritual authority to 
