for one soviets have terrible overhangs of money 
disproportionately high savings due to a lack of goods for 
consumers to purchase he said that means making the ruble 
convertible to foreign currencies could prompt high inflation 
poland by comparison had suffered years of rampant inflation 
that ate up savings and has started to subside under the reforms 
sachs said 
he said the soviet union could lower the money supply by setting 
a limit on savings acount withdrawals by doubling both wages and 
prices or even by confiscation 
in addition poland is much further along in decentralizing 
