<TEXT>
gerald e mowery retired chief of 
communications for the associated press in ohio died early monday 
after an illness that lasted several months he was 78 
mowery a native of lawton okla joined the ap as a junior 
operator in columbus in 1929 he advanced to the position of 
automatic operator before moving into the technical field 
he transferred to albuquerque nm in 1938 and returned to 
columbus a year later 
in 1957 mowery was named ohio traffic bureau chief the title 
then used for the ap technical department the title was later 
changed to chief of communications he retired in 1976 
mowery is survived by his wife kay two sons gerald of 
washington dc and william of sunbury ohio a daughter 
kathleen baumann of grandview in suburban columbus 19 
grandchildren and 34 greatgrandchildren 
