denvers other major air carrier united airlines 
the agreement calls for continental to enter a 20year lease 
with denver for 30 gates and 15 commuter plane parking spaces at 
the airport the airline will enter a separate 30year lease to 
repay the city for 100 million worth of support facilities that 
will be built by the city and used by continental at the new 
airport the support facilities will include a maintenance 
facility a cargo building and a flight kitchen 
the agreement will save continental from having to obtain its 
own financing to build the facilities and from paying millions of 
dollars in interest 
instead the city will float revenue bonds to pay for the 
building project and continental will repay the city 
