<TEXT>
television and radio stations in san 
francisco and charleston sc won peabody awards march 15 for 
their coverage of natural disasters last year while cbs radio news 
and cable news network were honored for their reporting of the 
student uprising in china 
the annual awards for distinguished broadcasting were announced 
by the university of georgia college of journalism and mass 
communication the 27 recipients will be presented the awards april 
3 in atlanta 
kcbsam and kgotv in san francisco were named as peabody 
winners for their reports of last octobers earthquake 
the peabody judges called the kcbs coverage comprehensive 
intelligent and useful while kgos reports were lauded for 
functioning as an information clearinghouse for viewers 
wcsctv in charleston covered hurricane hugo in a way that 
provided a lifeline for viewers deprived of water communications 
and other essential services the judges said 
other winners included broadcasting pioneer j leonard reinsch 
and veteran abc newsman david brinkley for distinguished careers in 
broadcasting 
the 50yearold awards are named for george foster peabody a 
columbus ga native who became a banker and philanthropist in new 
york 
here is the complete list of winners 
kcbsam san francisco for earthquake 89 which the 
judges called comprehensive intelligent and useful coverage of 
the october 1989 disaster 
cbs radio new york for china in crisis described as 
exhaustive coverage of the extraordinary events in china as they 
unfolded before a shocked world 
national public radio washington dc for scott simons 
radio essays presented on weekend edition saturday described 
as insightful thoughtprovoking and evocative commentary on 
american life 
canadian broadcasting corp in toronto for lost innocence 
the children of world war ii termed by judges a stirring 
recollection of the horror of war as seen through the eyes of 
youth 
d roberts independent producer american public radios 
soundprint series for mei mei a daughters song which 
judges called a poignant examination of the cultural gap between 
a daughter and her foreignborn mother 
texaco inc and the metropolitan opera association inc 
honoring a halfcentury of continuous saturday afternoon radio 
broadcasts the longest continuing sponsorship of a national 
program in broadcasting history 
wcsctv charleston sc for providing a lifeline for 
viewers deprived of water communications and other essential 
services after hurricane hugo 
kgotv san francisco for public service after the 1989 
earthquake functioning as an information clearinghouse for 
viewers 
kingtv seattle for project home team which judges 
called an examination of the wrenching problems of the working 
poor and how their lot can be improved 
krontv san francisco for i want to go home described by 
judges as a gripping and tragic account of the plight of homeless 
children in san francisco 
cable news network atlanta for coverage of the china crisis 
a series of thorough dramatic courageous and internationally 
important reports 
central independent television london for cambodia year 
ten called by the judges a passionate and strident examination 
of the plight of the asian nation from the barbarous pol pot regime 
to its tenuous present and uncertain future 
music television mtv new york for decade a look at the 
1980s as seen through the eyes of music performers and newsmakers 
cbs television and motownpangaea productions in association 
with quintex entertainment for the television miniseries 
lonesome dove described by the judges as a compelling drama 
of the old west which proved that the western is not dead 
abc television and blackmarlens co in association with new 
world television for the wonder years which the judges called 
an innovative humorous and often touching series about 
adolescence and family life in the tumultuous 1960s 
abc television and sacret inc in association with warner 
bros television for china beach vets an episode which 
recounted the experience of american nurses in vietnam in 
compelling chilling and emotional terms 
abc television lou rudolph films motown productions and 
allarcom and fries entertainment for the miniseries small 
sacrifices which judges said is a classic example of how 
exceptional acting coupled with a great script can provide 
television that is powerful and emotionally charged 
beyond international group sydney australia for the great 
wall of iron a behindthescenes examination of the chinese 
peoples liberation army completed only weeks before the 
infamous events in tianamen square 
hbo new york for common threads stories from the quilt 
which judges said is a stirring elegy to the victims of aids 
which celebrates their lives without exploiting their horrible and 
untimely deaths 
kcnctv denver for yellowstone four seasons after fire 
an indepth look at the park after the fire of 1988 and an 
examination of its recovery 
public affairs television new york for the public mind 
bill moyers critical look at public opinion formation and change 
in america and how the media affect basic social institutions 
wloxtv biloxi miss for did they die in vain an 
examination of mississippis progress in race relations during the 
past 25 years which the judges said demonstrates what a small 
market television with a capable and dedicated staff can contribute 
to the understanding of issues that are both complex and 
important 
film news nowthe american documentary new york for who 
killed vincent chin called by the judges a penetrating 
examination of a murder in detroit revealing the racism class 
conflict and media power which permeate modern america 
childrens television workshop new york for sesame 
street for what the judges described as two decades of 
innovative and effective education through the medium of 
television 
nbc news new york for nbc news special to be an 
american which the judges said sparks pride in what this 
country stands for and which validates the continuing contributions 
of an able and dedicated newsman tom brokaw 
david brinkley of abctv a personal award attesting to the 
exceptional contributions he has made to broadcasting during his 
tenure as one of this countrys richest treasures 
j leonard reinsch a pioneer in broadcasting cable and 
political communication for a lifetime of outstanding service to 
his chosen profession 
