had this image in movies and television of prosecutors being tough 
older and male i learned young lawyers spend six or seven years as 
prosecutors then move on the salaries are low the work is 
intense the burnout rate is high 
these people have such an overwhelming caseload that people 
fall through the cracks our show is about the cracks carter 
