acting in series 
race may be a problem for other people but i dont let it 
hold me back he said i dont look upon myself as a black 
director im a director being a director is very personal 
because you take with you your life and your experiences and your 
views and being africanamerican is an aspect of my character but 
its not the sum of my life 
im interested in so many things that are universal how the 
death of a person affects someone else love and relationships i 
want to explore a variety of themes as well as a variety of visual 
styles i think if you could sum up my work at all you could say 
it has a sense of romantic realism 
in the beginning carter knew he wanted to do a gritty urban 
show about the criminal justice system he wanted it to have an 
edge be fastpaced and have a mixture of humor and dark tragedy 
he returned to houston for more research then to new york 
where he visited all the boroughs and to chicago he also talked 
to some prosecutors in los angeles although he wanted the story 
set in an older city the pilot movie was filmed in pittsburgh 
in our show we dont deal just with the nuts and bolts of the 
law but with the politics of it as well said carter i wanted 
to do a show that would cause the american public never to look at 
the law the same again 
carter grew up in texas where he studied theater at southwest 
texas state university 
one of his first roles was as ray gun in szysznyk which 
disappeared before anyone learned how to pronounce it 
next came the white shadow where he got his chance to 
direct he found it more challenging than acting and began to 
direct many episodes of hill street blues and st elsewhere 
i was surprised when i directed because i didnt think i 
would like it he said i came here to act i thought if i 
directed at all it would be much later 
