<TEXT>
again an anniversary terry andersons fifth 
as a captive again a cycle of hopeful signs and statements about 
the american hostages in lebanon 
but optimism has proved hollow too often to come easily to the 
families colleagues and friends of anderson and the other seven 
americans held captive by militant moslem factions 
always before cycles of hope have yielded to cycles of 
frustration and silence this time perhaps it will be different 
peggy say andersons sister thinks so she is she says 
absolutely convinced that the ceremony held last friday across the 
street from the white house will be the last before anderson and 
other captives finally are freed 
anderson chief middle east correspondent of the associated 
press was seized by moslem gunmen on march 16 1985 he has been 
held longer than any other hostage his kidnappers identified 
themselves as members of a group called islamic jihad or holy war 
they are aligned with iran and two hostages who had been held with 
anderson were released after secret reagan administration arms 
shipments to the iranians 
the scandal over the arms sales and diversion of the proceeds to 
support contra rebels in nicaragua made the hostage situation part 
of the major political embarrassment of the reagan years president 
reagan had after all defeated a democratic president undercut by 
the iranian hostage crisis and had promised that he would not let 
americans be taken without swift and sure retribution 
there was no way to make good on that when shiite moslem 
factions began seizing american and other foreign hostages amid the 
unrelenting chaos in beirut all told there are now 18 foreign 
hostages in lebanon 
as he took office bush urged the iranians to help gain freedom 
for the hostages saying that goodwill would beget goodwill 
at milestones along the way anniversaries birthdays the 
release of other hostages the bush inauguration to succeed reagan 
the death of irans ayatollah khomeini there have been cycles of 
heightened public interest of speculation and sometimes of 
optimism about the release of hostages 
in the latest round which began about a month ago a leading 
moslem cleric in beirut said that a way should be found to free the 
hostages and iranian president hashemi rafsanjani was said to have 
declared that he would like the captives released 
but the moslem leader had said much the same thing more than a 
year ago near the fourth anniversary of andersons kidnapping 
rafsanjani as speaker of the iranian parliament had offered in 
1989 to help gain freedom for the hostages if the united states 
would work to free iranians believed to have been captured by 
lebanese christians 
but there have been changes along with those similarities 
president bush has put the hostage issue on the administrations 
public agenda in a way the reagan white house would not especially 
after the irancontra scandal broke 
he spent a half hour with mrs say and her husband david on 
friday bush policy does not break with the course set in the 
reagan years but his handling of the problem certainly does 
i intend to keep open lines of communications with all 
parties including iran who have influence over hostage takers 
bush said in a letter to mrs say please be assured that your 
government will take advantage of all legitimate opportunities to 
obtain the safe release of all of our hostages 
bush also said he had been in touch with syrian president hafez 
assad regarding the hostages his spokesman said later that was 
through diplomatic channels and that there have been other 
overtures to middle eastern leaders on the hostage situation 
jimmy carter met with assad last week and bush said he had 
received reports from the former president carter said in damascus 
that assad told him syria was seeking to convince the captors the 
hostages should be protected and released 
carter said in damascus on friday that he thinks there is a 
better chance of andersons release than ever before he said that 
stems in part from a growing desire on the part of iran and the 
united states to settle their differences 
for all the differences in this cycle of hope there are 
similarities to those that went before there are more contacts 
and changing circumstances but there is nothing firm only an 
atmosphere and conjecture 
bush said that he had been confused by all the speculation about 
a possible break in the hostage situation we are going down 
every alley we are trying every avenue to free the hostages but 
there is no negotiation going on he said 
