nat turners rebellion he could read in 1831 was used as a 
horrible example teaching slaves became illegal after the war the 
politically powerful wanted to keep taxes low why waste money on 
inferiors landlords didnt want sharecroppers reading the fine 
print at the company store let em grow cotton 
the paradox of an illeducated state producing faulkners and 
eudora weltys and richard wrights arises from the oral traditions 
of both the english yeomen and their african slaves wilson 
explains the traditions and histories of both people were handed 
down by storytellers but that is not book learning 
then in the 1980s there was some kind of transformation in 
