<TEXT>
at khe sanh the north vietnamese artillery bombardments reached 
more than 1000 rounds on some days american marines were at their 
very best under the worst conditions dragging bleeding comrades 
toward bunkers pleading corpsman corpsman weve got wounded 
here withstanding a 77day siege that inflicted nearly 2000 
casualties onethird of the entire garrison in the end they 
abandoned it 
jacque navarra rhoads who coedited the book nurses in 
vietnam the forgotten veterans at age 22 had come straight from 
nursing school in albion ny to tend to the shattered bodies in 
the monsoons and mud 
its really depressing because of the amputations she would 
say what a waste of men if i knew what we were fighting for if 
the enemy did something to our country i could see it i dont 
know why were here so many gis ask why i cant answer i came 
because they needed medical help i wanted to appreciate things 
better back home like clean sheets running water and a happy 
family 
