about it four days later a piece of steel from a north vietnamese 
rocket tore through her aorta she bled to death less than a month 
before her 26th birthday the first of eight women killed by 
hostile fire in vietnam 
like many veterans rod kane felt lonely and out of place a war 
that no one wanted turned him into an outcast a man who felt he 
had nothing to offer and was unworthy of returning to society 
