has seen not happy about the way it all ended but certainly 
proud that theyd served their country and i think that represents 
the true feeling of most vietnam vets 
michael norman says war puts a lie to the notion that men fight 
for a flag and they fight for their country they fight to stand 
by the man on their right or left the people that theyre close to 
at the moment and they fight to survive 
