<TEXT>
eastern airlines announced monday it was cutting 
first class fares by about 40 percent in an effort to attract more 
business travelers and was sweetening travel agent commissions for 
sales of the new cutrate tickets 
the lower fares called ynot fares are good for domestic 
travel through june 30 carry no penalties are fully refundable 
and can be booked up to flight time 
with the ynot fare you can buy them at anytime and fly at 
anytime said george brennan vice president of marketing for the 
miamibased carrier 
some industry analysts expressed surprise at the size of the 
fare cuts which put easterns firstclass tickets about 15 percent 
below the industrys full coach fares but they said they did not 
expect other carriers to immediately match or lower their rates 
its a marketing move a promotional program said robert 
decker analyst with duff amp phelps in chicago we might see some 
selective matching by other airlines but i wouldnt expect a 
widespread move at this point 
eastern is reorganizing under bankruptcy court protection from 
creditors where it sought protection following a crippling strike 
by pilots machinists and flight attendants a year ago 
decker said easterns success in emerging from bankruptcy 
depends on getting business travelers back in significant numbers 
theyre trying to get the business traveler back on and fill 
up the first class section which is probably flying empty right 
now decker said 
eastern claims its 9000 daily firstclass seats are 65 percent 
full although brennan conceded at a new york news conference that 
many passengers now flying first class on eastern are frequent 
flier passengers upgraded from coach 
current industry first class fares between new york and miami 
are 437 oneway while the lowest fullcoach fare is 333 
according to figures supplied by eastern the new ynot fare on 
that route is 276 one way 10 above easterns current fullcoach 
fare 
between chicago and atlanta the current firstclass oneway 
fare is 537 fullcoach is 360 and easterns ynot fare is 298 
eastern passengers with fullcoach fare tickets will be able to 
exchange their tickets for firstclass seats for 10 more 
easterns fullcoach fares the lowest in the industry are 10 
less than the ynot fares 
eastern said it expects the lower fares to generate about 
400000 a day more in net revenue the fares are good for travel 
in the united states puerto rico and the virgin islands 
andrew geller analyst with provident national bank in 
philadelphia said the increase in travel agent commissions will 
help eastern improve relations between the carrier and its travel 
agents 
standard commissions industrywide amount to about 10 percent 
eastern will boost the commissions on ynot tickets to 15 
percent 
many agents have been wary of putting customers on eastern 
because of the carriers financial problems 
some travel agents have not been booking on eastern for fear 
that in the future clients might get stranded geller said by 
doing this it tries to get around that fear 
