<TEXT>
soybean futures prices rose sharply monday on the 
chicago board of trade amid talk of lowerthanexpected brazilian 
soybean yields and diminishing fears that brazils economic reforms 
will lead to a flood of soybean marketings 
on other commodity markets coffee sugar and cocoa futures fell 
sharply livestock and meat futures advanced petroleum futures 
were mixed and precious metals were higher 
soybean futures settled 6 cents to 8 cents higher with march at 
590 a bushel 
the soybean market opened lower on expectations that sweeping 
economic reforms announced last week in brazil the worlds 
secondlargest soybean producer would stimulate farmer sales of 
soybeans there 
of greatest concern was a plan to replace brazils currency the 
cruzado novo with a new currency the cruzeiro which would 
feature freefloating foreign exchange rates many experts believe 
the cruzeiro will be sharply devalued which would prompt farmers 
to sell soybeans to obtain dollars or other hard currency 
but analysts saw no significant increase in brazilian sales over 
the weekend or on monday said steve freed a grain market analyst 
with dean witter reynolds inc 
meanwhile analysts said memphisbased sparks commodities inc 
released an estimate of the brazilian soybean crop pegging 
production at 195 million metric tons instead of the 205 million 
projected last month by the us agriculture department 
sparks would not confirm the number but analysts said 
indications of lowerthanexpected brazilian soybean yields the 
harvest began about two weeks ago have prompted a great deal of 
speculation that the crop will be smaller than the usdas estimate 
the smaller the brazilian crop the less it will compete with 
our beans once we get into the new crop year at the beginning of 
