<TEXT>
japans central bank on tuesday raised its official 
discount rate by 1 percentage point to 525 percent effective 
immediately 
the decision followed a meeting of the bank of japans special 
policy board officials said 
the nations discount rate the lending rate the central bank 
charges on loans to commercial banks was 425 percent following 
three hikes last year 
the rate increase was aimed at containing inflationary pressure 
building up in japan despite three interest hikes last year the 
jump in the rates was widely rumored for weeks 
the central bank action is also expected to help stabilize the 
jittery tokyo stock market and to stem the yens weakness against 
the us dollar 
