federal regulators monday agreed to allow the 
sale of most assets of the pittsburgh amp lake erie co railroad 
without requiring protection of workers who would lose their jobs 
the interstate commerce commission voted 41 against requiring 
more help for workers than the acquirer railroad development 
corp already has promised 
railroad development on suburban green tree has said it will 
offer the jobs it retains to current pample employees in order of 
seniority it also will credit those rehired with their years of 
service and negotiate new contracts with their unions 
the company told the commission it plans to retain a work force 
of 150 to 200 rather the the 417 nonmanagement workers currently 
working 
dan vogel president of local 1427 of the transport workers 
union at pample and a freight car repairman called the vote 
unfortunate we have to find out if rdc is willing to negotiate a 
fair and reasonable agreement he said 
railroad development is paying 33 million for 1466 miles of 
the pample line in ohio and pennsylvania more than 2200 freight 
cars and locomotives and the rights to use other railroads tracks 
in several states 
